Description: The Temptation of St Antony, with two temptresses and two devils, and God the Father flying down to his rescue; after Tintoretto. 1582 Engraving
Curator's comments: Plate described in 'Tintoretto e suoi incisori', Milan, 1994, cat. No.1, page 19-20. this is the first state, with Bertelli's address.
Bibliographic references: Bohlin 1979 / Prints and related drawings by the Carracci family (101.I)
Exhibition history: 2013 March-June, Madrid, Museo Nacional del Prado, ‘El trazo español en el British Museum …’
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (With Philipe's blindstamp and initials (washed out))
